==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mariposa lily
<hw>Ma`ri*po"sa lil`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Sp. <ets>mariposa</ets> a
butterfly + E. <ets>lily</ets>. So called from the gay appearance of the
blossoms.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of a genus
(<gen>Calochortus</gen>) of tuliplike bulbous herbs with large, and
often gaycolored, blossoms. Called also <altname>butterfly
lily</altname>. Most of them are natives of California.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mariput</ent>⟦br⟧
